title: 103_hr2761
content: Ocean and Coastal Management Improvement Act of 1993 - Transfers to the Department of the Interior the following offices and assets of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration: (1) the National Ocean Service, (2) the National Marine Fisheries Service, (3) the Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research, (4) the fleet of research and survey vessels. And (5) the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Corps. Transfers to the Department of Environmental Protection (sic) components of the National Ocean Service that carry out coastal management and assessment programs.
